  "text": "Now we are ready to formulate c e = c e (T ) for T = T (V r (R[x 1 , . . . , x m ]) ). This result generalizes [CITATION_1] Proposition 3.7] . Since c e = 0 for all e 2 when m r + 1, the formula in the following proposition is most meaningful when m − r − 1 > 0.",
